ходил, как я устал, мать!</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>how much I walked, how tired I am, mother!</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Munk."/><biblScope>82</biblScope></bibl></example><example><quote>fællady dwag</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>божество усталых</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>deity of the tired</q></tr><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru"> (?)</note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en"> (?)</note><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_СОПам."/><biblScope>IV 122</biblScope></bibl></example></exampleGrp><exampleGrp><example><quote>jæ kʼах næ fællad</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>его нога не уставала</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>his leg did not get tired</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Коста"/><biblScope>50</biblScope></bibl></example><example><quote>bafællad kæwynæj binonty kæstær</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>устал от плача младший член семьи</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>the younger family member is tired of crying</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Коста"/><biblScope>45</biblScope></bibl></example><example><quote>fyng... wazægæn jæ fællad safy</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>(накрытый) стол устраняет усталость гостя</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>a set table removes the fatigue of a guest</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Коста"/><biblScope>105</biblScope></bibl></example><example><quote>су cyd fækodton, су fællad badæn, æna!</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>как (много) я ходил, как я устал, мать!</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>how much I walked, how tired I am, mother!</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Munk."/><biblScope>82</biblScope></bibl></example><example><quote>fællady dwag</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>божество усталых</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>deity of the tired</q></tr><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru"> (?)</note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en"> (?)</note><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_СОПам."/><biblScope>IV 122</biblScope></bibl></example></exampleGrp><etym xml:lang="ru">Вероятно, восходит к <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><lang/> <w>*para-mrā-</w></mentioned> через ступени %i*fæl-mra%i → %ifæl-ra-%i → %ifælla-%i. Глагол %imra-%i ← %imla-%i ← %imle-%i ← %imel-%i — общеиндоевропейский. Исходное значение — ‘размягчать(ся) путем мятия, дубления, растирания’. Ср. <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/> <w>mrā-</w> <gloss><q>размягчать</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="ae"><w/> <gloss><q>дубить</q></gloss></mentioned>,  (в <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/> <w>mrātəm čarəma</w> <gloss><q>дубленая кожа</q></gloss></mentioned>), <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/> <w>mla-</w> <gloss><q>становиться вялым, дряблым</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/> <gloss><q>слабеть</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/> <gloss><q>млеть</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="ga"><lang/> <w>mláith</w> <gloss><q>мягкий</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="ga"><w/> <gloss><q>нежный</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><lang/> <w>βλάξ</w> <gloss><q>слабый</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="grc"><w/> <gloss><q>вялый</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><w/> <gloss><q>ленивый</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="la"><lang/> <w>flaccus</w> <gloss><q>дряблый</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="la"><w/> <gloss><q>вислый</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="la"><w/> <gloss><q>вислоухий</q></gloss></mentioned>, . Исходя из метатезы %i*mle-%i || %i*mel-%i, относят сюда же индоевропейские слова со значением ‘молоть’, ‘мельница’ (<mentioned xml:lang="cu"><lang/> <w>млѣти</w> <gloss><q>молоть</q></gloss></mentioned> и пр.). Вс. %sМиллер%s (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."/><biblScope>64</biblScope></bibl>) делит %ifæ-llajyn%i на %ifæ-mlā-y-un%i, забывая, что для осетинского надо исходить из формы %imrā-%i, а не %imlā-%i (ср. <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/> <w>mrā-</w></mentioned>); а в этом случае появление %iI%i остается необъяснимым. Если же исходить из %ifæl-mrā-%i, то %ill%i окажется естественным результатом упрощения и ассимиляции группы %i-lmr-%i.</etym><etym xml:lang="en">It probably traces back to <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><lang/> <w>*para-mrā-</w></mentioned> through the stages %i*fæl-mra%i → %ifæl-ra-%i → %ifælla-%i. The verb %imra-%i ← %imla-%i ← %imle-%i ← %imel-%i is a general Indo-European verb. The initial meaning is ‘soften by crushing, tanning, rubbing’. Cf. <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/> <w>mrā-</w> <gloss><q>soften</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="ae"><w/> <gloss><q>tan</q></gloss></mentioned>,  (in <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/> <w>mrātəm čarəma</w> <gloss><q>tanned leather</q></gloss></mentioned>), <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/> <w>mla-</w> <gloss><q>become faded, flabby</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/> <gloss><q>weaken</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/> <gloss><q>faint</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="ga"><lang/> <w>mláith</w> <gloss><q>soft</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="ga"><w/> <gloss><q>tender</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><lang/> <w>βλάξ</w> <gloss><q>weak</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="grc"><w/> <gloss><q>flabby</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><w/> <gloss><q>lazy</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="la"><lang/> <w>flaccus</w> <gloss><q>flaccid</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="la"><w/> <gloss><q>lop-eared</q></gloss></mentioned>, . Basing on the metathesis %i*mle-%i || %i*mel-%i, some people relate to it Indo-European words with the meaning ‘grind’, ‘mill’ (<mentioned xml:lang="cu"><lang/> <w>млѣти</w> <gloss><q>grind</q></gloss></mentioned> и пр.). Ws. %sMiller%s (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."/><biblScope>64</biblScope></bibl>) divides %ifæ-llajyn%i into %ifæ-mlā-y-un%i, forgetting that for Ossetic one should base on the form %imrā-%i, not on the %imlā-%i (cf. <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/> <w>mrā-</w></mentioned>); and in this case the appearance of %iI%i remains unexplained. On the contrary, if one bases on %ifæl-mrā-%i, then %ill%i will turn out to be a natural result of the simplification and assimilation of the group %i-lmr-%i.</etym></entry></body></text></TEI>